Service Model of Cloud (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS)



* Deployment Models of the Cloud

1) Private Cloud

Cloud service used by single organization.

Not exposed publicly.

Example: Rackspace


2) Public Cloud

Owned and operated by third-party providers.

Example: AWS, Azure, GCP


3) Hybrid Cloud

Some data/resources in private, some in public.

Example: AWS 

Secure Shell Protocol (Authenticate)



Diagram:

(Private Key)            (Public Key)
Client ────────────────► [Server]
 

* Note

Client has: Private Key

Server has: Public Key



